metadata.name: tied #96
metadata.description:
"tied" is trying to represent the feeling of pressure over people.
To represent that I did an abstraction with points trapped by lines and dense textures, some of these points is stucked in the middle of the road, trying to get out of the background to reach surface.


this is my last contribution to fx beta.

a project made with p5.js and love to make part of it.


Omar Lobato Neto, 19/03/2022

metadata.name: Planar #158
metadata.description: In this artwork, two-dimensional shapes have been treated with colors, stroke, texture, and rotation to give an illusion of volume. The underlying algorithm uses flow field mechanics to generate the arrangements on the screen. Because of this, it may sometimes take a few seconds to generate the artwork. The variations come out in different shapes that are rectangular, circular and elliptical.

metadata.name: Negative Space #325
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: Refractions #275
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #10
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.
